  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Admin Executive(Ecommerce)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Sales &amp; Traffic Generation</strong></p>\n<p>Set up and QA all promotions, pricing, promo codes and campaign assets on Guardian Online to maximise conversion and sales</p>\n<p>Coordinate with Marketing, Commercial and third-party agency &amp; partners (creatives, affiliates etc.) to brief offers and secure traffic‑driving exposure (EDM, push notifications, paid traffic etc.)</p>\n<p><strong>Content Management</strong></p>\n<p>Maintain accurate, locally relevant product and campaign content and site/app layouts</p>\n<p><strong>Post‑Sales Operations &amp; Customer Care</strong></p>\n<p>Liaise with Fulfilment Operations and Customer Service teams to deliver on‑time orders and speedy issue resolution</p>\n<p>Monitor KPIs and raise corrective actions when needed.</p>\n<p><strong>Reporting &amp; Continuous Improvement</strong></p>\n<p>Track campaign / banner performance, site metrics (CVR, bounce, basket, NPS) and competitor trends</p>\n<p>Recommend data‑led improvements</p>\n<p>Prepare and refresh business SOPs to ensure operational excellence and continuity</p>\n<p><strong>Job summary</strong></p>\n<p>Detail-oriented E-Commerce Admin to manage orders, inventory, logistics &amp; support, ensuring smooth operations &amp; customer satisfaction, help out with Marketing Team</p>",
